  "title": "Inside Sales Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Inside Sales Executive</strong></p><p>We are looking for a proactive and detail-oriented Inside Sales Executive to support our sales function through the management of box sales, smaller project engagements, and value-added service offerings. This role plays an important part in driving revenue efficiency while providing strong support to the wider sales team.</p><p><strong>The Responsibilities</strong></p><p>•\tManaging end-to-end box sales activities, including pricing requests, quotation preparation, and client follow-ups for product-only purchases</p><p>•\tPromoting and supporting sales of value-added services (e.g. Miro) to increase service adoption and revenue contribution</p><p>•\tHandling smaller project engagements, typically involving one to two rooms, from quotation to handover</p><p>•\tActing as a support function to the sales team by taking ownership of smaller-value quotations and transactions</p><p>•\tContributing to overall business performance by achieving assigned sales targets and increasing service uptake</p><p>•\tOperating under the sales function with responsibility for independent pricing and quotation management for box sales</p><p>•\tParticipating in training, coaching, and knowledge transfer sessions conducted by senior sales personnel</p><p>•\tMaintaining accurate documentation, records, and follow-ups related to sales activities</p><p><strong>Pre-Requisites:</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma / Advanced / Higher / Graduate Diploma in any field</p><p>•\tExperience in inside sales, sales support, or a customer-facing role is an advantage</p><p>•\tExposure to AV, IT, or technology-related products and services will be beneficial</p><p>•\tComfortable with pricing, quotations, and sales documentation</p><p>•\tStrong communication and coordination skills</p><p>•\tWell-organised, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple tasks</p><p>•\tPositive attitude, strong work ethic, and willingness to learn</p><p>•\tTeam player who can work independently with minimal supervision</p><p></p>",
